The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Reyna will be ready, says US coach

Hamburg: US captain Claudio Reyna will be fit to face the Czech Republic in the World Cup on June 12, coach Bruce Arena said on Saturday. 

Arena told reporters at the US team hotel that midfielder Reyna fully participated in training, as did midfielder John Brien who is working to gain match fitness after playing only sporadically since the 2002 finals. 

I think hes really going to be ready on June 12, said Arena of the opening fixture of the US World Cup campaign when they meet the Czech Republic in Gelsenkirchen. 

Manchester Citys Reyna injured a hamstring on May 23 in a friendly against Morocco. He has not played since. 

